cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.DS 

The paper deals with analyzing networks of "persons of interest" from various sources, including law-enforcement agencies and financial institutions. This suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data mining (cs.DS), security and privacy (cs.CR), and possibly machine learning (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed model, Cliqster, is a generative model for unweighted networks, which involves community structure and maximum likelihood solutions, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI) or algorithms and data structures (cs.SD).
